    <p>{`An Ethereum node is required when trading on Ethereum-based decentralized exchanges or protocols. There are different ways you can access an Ethereum node.`}</p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://infura.io/"
        }}>{`Infura`}</a>{` provides free and the most widely used Ethereum node. Their blog post below provides more information, including how to access:`}
        <ul parentName="li">
          <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
              "href": "https://blog.infura.io/getting-started-with-infura-28e41844cc89/"
            }}>{`Getting started with Infura`}</a></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li parentName="ol"><strong parentName="li">{`Running your own local node.`}</strong>{` It may require dedicated storage and compute, as well as some technical skills. Note that these may require several hours to sync and may require some troubleshooting when first running. These are the two most widely used Ethereum clients:`}
        <ul parentName="li">
          <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
              "href": "https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Building-Ethereum"
            }}>{`Geth (go-ethereum)`}</a></li>
          <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
              "href": "https://github.com/paritytech/parity-ethereum"
            }}>{`Parity`}</a></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li parentName="ol"><strong parentName="li">{`Using dedicated blockchain hardware.`}</strong>{` Ethereum nodes are meant to constantly run 24/7 and use up a material amount of computational resources (CPU, RAM, and storage). For more serious users, it may make sense to use dedicated hardware.`}
        <ul parentName="li">
          <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
              "href": "https://dappnode.io/"
            }}>{`DAppNode`}</a>{` is software that automates the installation and operation of Ethereum (as well as other blockchains) on dedicated hardware. It is easier to start and operate an Ethereum node and can run other blockchains.`}</li>
          <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
              "href": "https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/products/boards-kits/nuc.html"
            }}>{`Intelâ“‡ NUC mini PC`}</a>{` : DIY, customize and configure your own hardware`}</li>
          <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
              "href": "https://ava.do/"
            }}>{`Avado`}</a>{` : purpose-built hardware that is pre-loaded with DAppNode`}</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ol>
